Reads the given files (tweets_aa, tweets_ab, tweets_ac) and returns the count breakdown in areas for the search keyword
Keep tweets.py and the given files in the same directory

EXAMPLE:
$ python tweets.py knicks

OUTPUT:
Count results for 'knicks'

In 'tweets_ac':
Bronx 16
Brooklyn 12
Staten Island 11
Manhattan 13
Queens 13
TOTAL: 65

In 'tweets_ab':
Bronx 13
Brooklyn 19
Staten Island 8
Manhattan 58
Queens 21
TOTAL: 119

In 'tweets_aa':
Bronx 20
Brooklyn 31
Staten Island 10
Manhattan 53
Queens 42
TOTAL: 156

GRAND TOTAL: 340